Business Brief -- La Quinta Motor Inns Inc.:
   Official Sells Large Portion
   Of His Holdings in Concern
The San Antonio, Texas, owner and operator of motels said
that a group including Thomas M. Taylor and members of Fort
Worth's Bass family purchased 500,000 of the shares,
increasing the group's La Quinta holding to 2.6 million
shares, or about a 20% stake.
   A group led by New Zealand financier Sir Ronald Brierley
purchased 500,000 shares, which would raise its stake to
roughly 18% of La Quinta's stock. GeoCapital Corp., an
investment adviser, bought 200,000 shares, raising its stake
to 12%.